<h1>@HI{{zutsu}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <em>quantifier</em>  <strong>@HI{{zutsu}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{zutsu}}</strong> is a particle that indicates that a quantity is equally distributed.
</br>

<strong>@HI{{zutsu}}</strong> always follows a quantifier.
</br>

If <strong>@HI{{zutsu}}</strong> is removed from the sentence the maning hardly changes. 
<strong>@HI{{zutsu}}</strong> serves only focus on the equal distribution.
</br>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{dono @KT{{kurasu}}ni mo @KJ{{woman^child^study^life}}ga @KJ{{six^person}} <strong>zutsu</strong> ita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      There were six girl students in each class.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

